cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.NE 

The paper deals with a deep learning framework for image reconstruction, specifically in the context of passive synthetic aperture radar (SAR). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) and unsupervised learning, which are common topics in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category. The paper also mentions optimization methods, which are relevant to the cs.IT (Information Theory) category. The use of RNNs for image reconstruction can also be considered a control problem, which falls under the cs.SY (Systems and Control) category. Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the proposed method in comparison to conventional sparse coding methods, which is relevant to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) category.
